<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22165] Type conflicts between dates, timestamps and date in partition column</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22165</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks we have some bugs when resolving type conflicts in partition column. I found few corner cases as below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Case 1: timestamp should be inferred but date type is inferred.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val df = Seq((1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;2015-01-01&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), (2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;2016-01-01 00:00:00&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)).toDF(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;i&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ts&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
df.write.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;parquet&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).partitionBy(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ts&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).save(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
spark.read.load(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).printSchema()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;root
 |-- i: integer (nullable = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)
 |-- ts: date (nullable = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Case 2: decimal should be inferred but integer is inferred.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val df = Seq((1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), (2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt; * 30)).toDF(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;i&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;decimal&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
df.write.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;parquet&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).partitionBy(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;decimal&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).save(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/bar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
spark.read.load(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/bar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).printSchema()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;root
 |-- i: integer (nullable = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)
 |-- decimal: integer (nullable = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks we should de-duplicate type resolution logic if possible rather than separate numeric precedence-like comparison alone.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
